value.value: The manufacturer of the assay.
The number of different analytes being measured simultaneously in a single sample.
The name of the assay.
The source of the performance statistics of an assay.
The replicate number of the assay, i.e. the numeric iteration for the assay that was repeated.
A set of statistical procedures designed to accumulate experimental and correlational results across independent studies that address a related set of research questions.
The type of a result that is reported in an assay.
The unit of measure of a result that is reported in an assay.
The antigenic component of interest in an assay.
The source of the antigenic component of interest in an assay.
The sub-region of the antigenic component of interest in an assay.
The type of a technology on which an assay is based.
An instrument that determines the numbers, types or viability of cells present in a sample.
The biospecimen collection company or clinic that obtains the sample.
The date that a biospecimen was collected.
The time that a biospecimen was collected.

The inevitable variety in customs, attitudes, practices, and behaviors that exists among groups of individuals from different ethnic, racial, or national backgrounds who come into contact within a social unit, organization, or population.
The initials of the person's name who collected the sample.
The cohort to which a collected biospecimen belongs.
A unique identifier assigned to a biological specimen.
The biospecimen processing company or clinic that prepares the sample.
The date that a biospecimen was processed.
The initials of the person's name who processed the sample.
The time that a biospecimen was received.
The type of calibration method used to verify that an assay or device is operating within normal parameters.
The high or positive reference standard used in the calibration of an assay or device.
The low or negative reference standard used in the calibration of an assay or device.

A constellation of responses that occur when an organism is exposed to excessive heat and other environmental stresses. Responses include synthesis of some proteins, repression of other proteins, and expression of new proteins. (From Segen, Dictionary of Modern Medicine, 1992)
Dimethyl sulfoxide that is ultra-purified to remove microbiological contaminants for specific use in cell culture.
The length of time a sample was centrifuged.
Body mass index (BMI) greater than 40.
The period of time during which cytomegalovirus infection persists.
The date that a cytomegalovirus molecular test was performed.
The outcome of cytomegalovirus molecular testing.
The origin of a cytomegalovirus molecular test result.
The date that a cytomegalovirus serology test was performed.
The outcome of cytomegalovirus serology testing.
The origin of a cytomegalovirus serology test result.

Immunoglobulin A secretion by mucosal epithelia in the gastrointestinal, respiratory, and genitourinary tracts. Mucosal immunity promotes resistance toward bacteria, viruses, and parasites in these ports of entry into the body.
The type of collection tube used to obtain the sample.
The catalog number of the collection tube type used to obtain the sample.
The date after which the collection tube type is no longer to be used.
The lot number of the collection tube type used to obtain the sample.
The catalog number of the consumable.
The date after which the consumable is no longer to be used.
The lot number of the consumable.
The name of the consumable.
A freezer that allows for uniform cooling by gradually decreasing the temperature over a preset period of time.
COVID-19 disease severity based on the World Health Organization's Ordinal Scale for Clinical Improvement (WHO 2020).

A recombinant chimeric, mouse-human monoclonal antibody directed against tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF-alpha), a protein involved in inflammation, cell survival, and apoptosis. Infliximab may be pro- apoptotic or anti-apoptotic, depending on cell type. (NCI04)
